# Description

Build a video bin instead of an audio bin, using one of the many interesting video filters GStreamer offers, like solarize, vertigotv or any of the Elements in the effectv plugin. Remember to use the color space conversion element videoconvert if your pipeline fails to link due to incompatible caps.

# Hint/Solution

Start by creating a diagram of what the current pipeline looks like.

Since the exercise description says to make a video bin, we right away know that we will no longer make use of the `equalizer` element. We're told to use a video filter element (I chose to use `vertigotv`), and we're also recommended to use a `videoconvert` element (which we know from earlier exercises that we do actually need).

Our new pipeline thus should look like this:
